The unit test code files are located in the directory:  
`\Capstone-Project21-main\client\src\__tests__`

Steps to Run Unit Tests:

1. Install Jest-related dependencies using npm:

   npm install --save-dev jest @testing-library/react @testing-library/jest-dom
   npm install --save-dev jest-environment-jsdom
   npm install --save-dev @babel/preset-react @babel/preset-env
   npm install --save-dev identity-obj-proxy
   npm install --save-dev @babel/core @babel/preset-env @babel/preset-react babel-jest identity-obj-proxy
   npm install --save-dev @testing-library/jest-dom


2. Add the following configuration to the `package.json` file:

   "scripts": {
     "test": "jest --config jest.config.js"
   }


3. Create the `jest.config.js` file in the root directory of the project (\Capstone-Project21-main\), with the following content:

   module.exports = {
       transform: {
           "^.+\\.jsx?$": "babel-jest"
       },
       testEnvironment: 'jest-environment-jsdom',
       moduleNameMapper: {
           "\\.(css|less)$": "identity-obj-proxy"
       }
   };


4. Create the `babel.config.js` file in the root directory of the project, with the following content:

   module.exports = {
       presets: [
           "@babel/preset-env",
           "@babel/preset-react"
       ]
   };


5. Run the tests using the following command:

   npm test
